				A DeFi liquidity pool is a smart contract that locks tokens on a decentralized exchange to guarantee certain tokens' liquidity. Users that have smart contract tokens are referred to as liquidity providers. The exchange functions as a market in this model, where buyers and sellers come together and negotiate on commodity values dependent on ...			</p>

